          "component_id": "gallery_character",
          "data": {
            "list": [
              {
                "img": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2023/12/19/94376896/34b593e084657469cf0796b081d5ec2c_2723573100085995083.png",
                "imgDesc": "<p>In the wilds of Fontaine, you may occasionally encounter these overly-lively — perhaps due to outside influences — contaminated bacterial mats. The contamination clots and contamination cores within can be <span style=\"color: #FFE14B\">cleansed</span> by the abilities of the Xenochromatic Ball Octopus and other <span style=\"color: #FFE14B\">Xenochromatic Fontemer Aberrants</span>.</p>",
                "key": "Page 1/3"
              },
              {
                "img": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2023/12/19/94376896/9c02da27cb1f09eac760a754e0da5aff_4104506169310246443.png",
                "imgDesc": "<p>Due to evolution, sometimes contamination clots will <span style=\"color: #FFE14B\">link</span> together with each other. If these connected contamination clots are not all cleansed, previously removed clots will <span style=\"color: #FFE14B\">regenerate</span>.</p><p>Some contamination cores will be protected by an <span style=\"color: #FFE14B\">impenetrable shell</span>, and the surrounding clots must all be cleansed before the shell is removed and the core can be attacked.</p>",
                "key": "Page 2/3"
              },
              {
                "img": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2023/12/19/94376896/37607a13eddbddf25d0079a805efbc25_5956125005133871056.png",
                "imgDesc": "<p>Some contamination cores have even evolved the ability to attack, and will defend themselves. Others may actively hunt, seeking more nutrients...</p>",
                "key": "Page 3/3"
              }
            ],
            "pic": ""
          }
        }
      ]
